# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECRETS TEMPLATE
#
# 1. Make a copy of this file and name the copy ".env"  (just .env, nothing else)
# 2. Put your real keys/passwords in the .env copy — NOT in this file.
# 3. The .env file is kept private and is never shared or uploaded.
#
# This .env.example file only lists the NAMES of the secrets your agent needs,
# so other people know what to fill in. It must never contain real values.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Add the secrets your agent needs below, one per line, like:
# EXAMPLE_API_KEY=your_key_here
# SERVICE_EMAIL=you@example.com
# SERVICE_PASSWORD=your_password_here

# ---- Email sending (tools/send_email.py) ----
# For Gmail: SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com, SMTP_PORT=587, SMTP_USER=<your @gmail.com>,
# and SMTP_PASSWORD = a Google *App Password* (NOT your normal password — create one at
# https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords, requires 2-Step Verification enabled).
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=you@example.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your_app_password_here
EMAIL_FROM=you@example.com
# SMTP_SECURITY=starttls   # starttls (port 587, default) | ssl (port 465) | none
